## Working Instructions

### Requirements

- Python [3.x] (recommend via Anaconda or Miniconda)
- See `environment.yml` for full dependency list

Key packages:
```
pandas
numpy
scipy
matplotlib
geopandas        # if using spatial layers
rasterio         # if using DEM or MODIS
jupyter
```

### Setup

**1. Clone this repository**
```bash
git clone https://github.com/[your-username]/[your-repo-name].git
cd [your-repo-name]
```

**2. Create and activate the conda environment**
```bash
conda env create -f environment.yml
conda activate boulder-snowmelt
```

*Or with pip:*
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

**3. Download raw data** *(if not included in repo)*

SNOTEL data:
```
Visit: https://www.nrcs.usda.gov/wps/portal/wcc/home/dataAccessHelp
Stations: [list your stations]
Variables: SWE, Snow Depth, Temperature
Period: [your date range]
Save to: data/raw/snotel/
```

USGS streamflow data:
```
Visit: https://waterdata.usgs.gov
Site(s): [your gauge number(s)]
Parameter: 00060 (Discharge, mean daily)
Period: [your date range]
Save to: data/raw/usgs/
```

### Running the Workflow

Run notebooks in order:

| Step | Notebook | Description |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | `01_data_acquisition.ipynb` | Downloads / loads raw data from APIs |
| 2 | `02_data_cleaning_eda.ipynb` | Cleans, aligns, and explores the data |
| 3 | `03_lag_analysis.ipynb` | Core analysis: lag correlation and timing metrics |
| 4 | `04_figures_results.ipynb` | Generates all final figures |

> All notebooks can be run top-to-bottom with no modifications, assuming data is in the expected directories.

